The small woolly bat (Kerivoula intermedia) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae.
It is found only in Malaysia and is little known. It is only slightly larger than the Kitti's hog-nosed bat, one of the smallest mammals in the world. The small woolly bat weighs 2.5 to 4 g (0.088 to 0.141 oz).